AllowPlayers is a simple plugin for bukkit which allows players access
to a server that runs in online mode when minecraft.net is down.

Commands:
    - allowplayers - Manage and view pending requests
        - Aliases: ap
        - Usage: /<command> [[pending|reload] [accept|reject]] [[pagenumber] [playername]]
    - mcnet - Minecraft.net management
        - Aliases: mcn
        - Usage: /<command> [status|force] [check|online|offline]
    - onlinemode - Sets the server's online mode state
        - Aliases: om
        - Usage: /<command> [status|enable|disable]
    
Permissions:
    - allowplayers.ap            - Access the allowplayers command
        - allowplayers.ap.mod    - Accept/reject a pending request
        - allowplayers.ap.reload - Reload the configuration
    - allowplayers.mcn           - Access the mcnet command
        - allowplayers.mcn.force - Force minecraft.net mode
    - allowplayers.onlinemode    - Set the server's online mode
    - allowplayers.msg.notify    - View Minecraft.net status messages
    - allowplayers.msg.request   - View messages about requests
